  "why": "The paper does not demonstrate or evaluate the transferability of the discovered fault-inducing inputs across independently trained models. The experiments focus on finding failures within a single model or its derivatives. For instance, one experiment finds inputs that cause numerical errors (NaNs) in a single trained network. Another key experiment finds disagreements between a 32-bit floating-point model and its 16-bit quantized version. While this involves two model versions, it is a form of differential testing where the disagreement itself is the objective, not a post-hoc test of transferability to an independently trained model. The metric's coding guidance explicitly states that using multi-model disagreement as a differential oracle does not constitute cross-model transferability. The other experiments also focus on single models or code implementations. Therefore, the paper does not show whether fault-inducing inputs discovered on one model also trigger failures in others.",
